beer.beer_description: Very pale straw with short lived white head. Not a lot of aroma - soft grain and maybe the slightest hint of grass. Medium body and nice mouth-filling carbonation. Flavour is pretty basic with some fairly pleasant soft light malt at the start, followed by some citrus tang and a hint of bitterness in the finish. Overall it is pleasant enough for an Asian pale lager - completely drinkable, and completely unmemorable.
